Random Forests Algorithm which is a version of ensemble learning 
el => take the same Algorithm multiple times and put them together to make something more powerful. 


Steps 1: Pick a random K datapoint from the training set. 

Step 2: Build a decision tree associated w that k data points. 

Step 3: Choose the number of Ntree of trees u want to build and repeat steps 1 and 2 

Step 4: for a new data pt, make sure one of your ntree trees predict the value of Y 
for the datapt in question and assign the new data pt the average across all of the predicted y value. 

instead of getting one prediction, get like 500 predictions for the value of y and take the average 
across those predictions and that improves the accuracy of the prediction. 